# CarPlay

Apply when changing in-car UI, scene setup, or how CarPlay lists relate to app state.

## JS entry

- **`lib/carplay.ts`** — `setupCarPlay()` / `teardownCarPlay()` register connect/disconnect handlers, build **TabBarTemplate** (Recently Played + Playlists), push playlist detail templates, enable now playing, and **subscribe to Zustand** so lists refresh when library/audio state changes.
- Wired from **`app/_layout.tsx`** after app readiness (mirroring teardown on unmount).

## Native iOS

- **`ios/Rite/CarPlaySceneDelegate.swift`** — `CPTemplateApplicationSceneDelegate`; on connect calls `RNCarPlay.connect(with:window:)`, on disconnect `RNCarPlay.disconnect()`.
- **`ios/Rite/PhoneSceneDelegate.swift`** — Ensures a normal **phone** window scene exists when the app also declares a CarPlay scene in `UIApplicationSceneManifest` (without this, the phone UI may not get a window scene).
- **`AppDelegate`** uses the phone scene delegate for the main window; CarPlay remains on `CarPlaySceneDelegate` via Info.plist.

## Dependencies

- Package: **`react-native-carplay`**. Artwork URLs for list rows should be **http/https** only; local `file://` art is skipped in list items (see `artworkUrlForCarPlay`).

## Playback

- Item selection resolves tracks through the same stores as the phone app (e.g. `playSound` from `useAudioStore`); do not duplicate queue logic inside CarPlay templates beyond calling existing actions.
